(29, 'What Are Tenses?', 'Explaining tenses, tense is a verb-based means of indicating the timing, and occasionally the continuance or completion, of an action or condition in connection to the period of speaking.\r\n\r\n', '', 'eng_tense.png', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/97ZgXLQxkpU?si=kcOiErb-yDqXCBt1', 'https://take.quiz-maker.com/QBERU1R2A', 'jenish', '2024-01-11', 3, 16, '#tenses', '00:04:12'),
(30, 'Rules Of Tenses', 'English phrases or sentences are formed using tenses rules. There are three forms of tenses: present tense, past tense, and future tense. The past relates to what happened much before, the present tense relates to what is occurring now, and the future tense relates to what will happen after now. They essentially depict temporal elements based on the actual timing.', '', 'eng_tens_rule.png', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/SEO9YPzSH-0?si=sblktUFvtCl_Z6R8', 'https://take.quiz-maker.com/Q5J7LFC76', 'jenu', '2024-01-11', 3, 16, '#rules', '00:11:27'),
(31, 'php features', 'Performance:\r\n\r\nPHP script is executed much faster than those scripts which are written in other languages such as JSP and ASP. PHP uses its own memory, so the server workload and loading time is automatically reduced, which results in faster processing speed and better performance.', 'PHP (Hypertext Preprocessor) is a widely-used server-side scripting language primarily designed for web development but also applicable for general-purpose programming. Here are some of the key features of PHP:\n\nEase of Use: PHP is relatively easy to learn and use, especially for beginners with a background in programming. Its syntax is similar to C-style languages like C, Java, and JavaScript, making it familiar to many developers.\n\nServer-Side Scripting: PHP is primarily used for server-side scripting, meaning PHP code is executed on the server to generate dynamic web content before being sent to the client\'s web browser. This allows developers to create interactive and data-driven web applications.\n\nOpen Source: PHP is open-source, meaning its source code is freely available for anyone to view, modify, and distribute. This has led to a large and active community of developers contributing to its development and maintenance.\n\nCross-Platform Compatibility: PHP runs on various platforms, including Linux, Windows, macOS, and others, making it suitable for developing web applications on different server environments.\n\nIntegration with Web Servers: PHP integrates seamlessly with popular web servers like Apache, Nginx, and Microsoft IIS, allowing developers to deploy PHP applications with ease.\n\nDatabase Integration: PHP has built-in support for interacting with databases, including MySQL, PostgreSQL, SQLite, and others. This allows developers to create dynamic web applications that store and retrieve data from databases.\n\nExtensive Standard Library: PHP comes with a comprehensive standard library that provides functions and modules for a wide range of tasks, including file I/O, database access, networking, session management, and more.\n\nFrameworks and Libraries: PHP has a rich ecosystem of frameworks and libraries that extend its functionality and simplify common tasks. Frameworks like Laravel, Symfony, CodeIgniter, and Zend Framework provide structure and tools for building scalable and maintainable web applications.\n\nTemplate Engine Support: PHP supports template engines like Smarty, Twig, and Blade, which help separate presentation logic from business logic, improving code maintainability and reusability.\n\nCommunity Support: PHP has a large and active community of developers who contribute to online forums, user groups, and open-source projects. This community provides support, resources, and collaboration opportunities for PHP developers worldwide.\n\nOverall, PHP\'s ease of use, server-side scripting capabilities, database integration, extensive standard library, and strong community support make it a popular choice for web development and other server-side programming tasks.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'php_feature.png', 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/vSYnrbeUKL0?si=wYRqABQB77A-wy7D', 'https://take.quiz-maker.com/QJKIAHHWU', 'piksu', '2024-01-15', 4, 3, '#features', '00:11:00');
